{
  "texts": [
    "Among various partitioning strategies (Kang et al., 2017; Zhang et al., 2020), layer-wise partitioning is the most widely adopted (Hauswald et al., 2014; Teerapittayanon et al., 2016; Kang et al., 2017; Teerapittayanon et al., 2017).",
    "In this approach, a deep neural network (DNN) is divided into two or more segments that are executed collaboratively across multiple devices.",
    "One of the earliest works in this direction, Hauswald et al.",
    "(Hauswald et al., 2014), proposed offloading the later stages of image classification computation to cloud servers.",
    "Following this, Neurosurgeon (Kang et al., 2017) and DDNN (Teerapittayanon et al., 2017) introduced automated frameworks to dynamically distribute DNN workloads between mobile devices and cloud servers, optimizing for factors such as network latency and energy efficiency."
  ]
}